Instead of devirtualization, a simpler optimization, which would additionally also help in the dynamic case, is simple loop hoisting of the method pointer fetch. Instead of doing<p><pre><code>    while(...) {
      (obj->vtable[0])(...)
    }
</code></pre>
we could have<p><pre><code>    void(*fn)(...) = obj->vtable[0]
    while(...) {
      fn(...)
    }
</code></pre>
which would avoid two redirections per inner loop! Actually, I&#x27;m almost sure that is what LuaJIT would do, and many other high-level programming languages could perform this optimization as well. However, maybe C is too low-level to be able to do that, and I don&#x27;t know about C++.
